texts.text: >You arrive at a rather ordinary-looking building.
This is apparently where the cult is headquartered.
It seems pretty big. There seem to be guards at the entrance as well.
Let's stick to the shadows and... Vince?! What are you doing?!
>Vince starts nonchalantly walking towards the entrance.
You really just gonna keep hiding like that?
Torture is what we're good at so...!
I really don't think that's the best idea...
C'mon, we're going.
Let's go.
Let's keep watching.
You too, Newbie?! I don't have a choice, do I...?
You say that, but Honey's waving us over.
There's no way we won't be found now...
We can't just let the two of them go alone like this.
We should go.
>As you head towards Vince's position,
>you begin picking up on the guards' conversation.
Our last plan didn't work, but we get to use "that" as the next sacrifice...!
Yes. The summon should already be underway, so just a little bit longer...!
A summon? Does that mean...?!
Who the hell are you?! You don't look like worshippers!
We're, um...
This the headquarters of the cult that's been killing all those people using demons?
V-Vince, wait!
What was that...?
You can talk now or after we've had some "alone time" together.
>Demons suddenly appear out of the back alley.
D-Demons?! They've come back to get revenge!
You... You made me... Imperfect...!
I'm sorry for not summoning you properly! Just don't kill me, please...!
>The demons mercilessly begin attacking the cultists!
*Scream*
>Their bodies are hewn to pieces in an instant.
Shit! Devil Download!
>Vince's demon lands a swift kick.
Gah... If only... My powers were... Full strength...
>The demon disappears.
>You rush to see how the cultists fared.
*Gag*

Geez...
Their torsos are...
They're goners.
Dammit. Two more to the body count.
They also mentioned something about "not summoning them properly"...
Maybe they messed up when they tried to summon their demons?
That means they need these demons for a reason.
One of them also said, "The summon is already underway..."
We gotta hurry before that body count goes up even more.
There's no one here...?
This feels way too cramped for a building as big as this.
>Vince finds a hidden door behind some bookshelves.
A hidden door...?!
Hey, this thing needs a password or something.
Coming right up!
I brought my laptop just in case something like this happened...
>Shiang Sun clatters away at his keyboard...
I'm liking this criminal vibe!
Vibe? He's way past that.
Cut me some slack! We don't have time to argue what's good or bad right now!
>A few seconds later...
It's open!
Oh, nicely done!
I'm guessing that was a piece of cake for him.
Sadly, it lacks any thrill when it's too easy.
They could've at least booby trapped it with a demon...
Tell us about your weird obsessions later. We gotta get going!
You're one to talk, Vince. You're Mr. Weird Obsessions himself...!
Hah. Keep talking.
>Honey peeks behind the hidden door.
I think it goes underground...
I'll take point. You guys follow me.
What on earth is this place...?!
It's so big.

And it smells funny...
Huh? Is that...?
>Shiang sees what appears to be the head of a large animal.
>Its eyes have been gouged out, its skin flayed and seems to be rotting.

And this is...
A mummified human finger?
>Vince finds a pile of shriveled human fingers on a shelf.

Well, um...
They could be fake...
They're real.
They're fake.
Please, don't...
S-See...
Honey saw everything.
There were a bunch of people at the entrance with their ring fingers missing.
Quiet. You hear that?
>You listen carefully and hear someone chanting...

Nyarl... Ath!
Nyarl...Na!
Is this the summoning ritual...? Let's hurry!
>As you go deeper, you hear the chant clearer and clearer.

Nyarl Sh'tan...
Nyarl G'shana...
>You also start to smell incense being burned...
What is this sweet but strange scent...?
So that's how they get people to join.
It's a drug, so don't breathe it in too much. A kid like you might not be able to handle it.
B-But...
>Shaing Sun covers his nose.
Now, it's time to put an end to this.
>The chant begins to gradually change.

Cthulhu Wgah'nagl!
Nyarlathotep Z'gah!
>As you open the doors,
>you see a hoard of cultists performing a summoning ritual.
Who's there?!
This is their summoning area?! We need to...
>A woman covered in blood lay upon the altar.
>You then see the person that seems to be leading the ritual.
>In their right hand is a knife.
>In the other hand is a still-beating heart.
Oh... God...
We need to call an ambulance... Or...
Intruders!
Reverend, leave them to us!
>The cultists attack the Liberators all at once...!
